<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Lower Import Duties on Three More Products </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0903131294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1251 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0903131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 9 (XINHUA) -- China will reduce the 
import duties on three more products in a bid to further ease 
the tax burdens of enterprises and promote production, according 
to the State Council Tax Rules Committee. 
  The three products are compressors for air conditioners, 
photocopying machine parts, and internal threaded copper pipes 
for air conditioner condensers. 
  The range of import duty reduction is between 10 percent and 
33 percent. 
  The new interim tariff rates will be implemented soon by 
China's customs. 

