  Rong said that China's economy would keep developing in a 
sustained, rapid and healthy way this year. 
  He also briefed the Finnish guests on the prospect of 
China's 
economic development. 
  They expressed the hope that China and Finland will enhance 
exchanges and cooperation in the fields of economics and trade, 
science and technology, education, environmental protection and 
tourism. 
  Chen Muhua, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, 
took 
part in the meeting. 
  Uosukainen arrived here on March 4 as guest of the NPC 
Standing Committee. She is scheduled to end her China visit 
today. 

